      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(slack): include attachment text in thread context",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\r\nSlack alert messages from monitoring bots can have an empty `message.text` while the actual alert content is stored in Slack `attachments` or Block Kit `blocks`.\r\nIn that case, OpenClaw's Slack thread context skipped the bot/root message as empty, so agents could not see the alert details in Slack threads.\r\n\r\n## Why This Change Was Made\r\nThe Slack thread starter/history resolver now derives fallback text from:\r\n- attachment fields: `pretext`, `title`, `text`, `fallback`\r\n- attachment `message_blocks`\r\n- top-level Slack `blocks`\r\nThis keeps monitoring bot alerts visible to the agent even when Slack does not populate `message.text`.\r\n\r\n## User Impact\r\nAgents in Slack alert channels can now read and triage bot-authored alert messages whose content is delivered through Slack attachments or blocks.\r\nThis specifically fixes monitoring-style Slack messages where the root thread message contains alert details only in attachments.\r\n\r\n## Evidence\r\n- Added tests for thread history preserving bot messages with text only in Slack attachments.\r\n- Added tests for thread history preserving bot messages with text only in Slack blocks.\r\n- Added tests for thread starter extracting root alert text from Slack attachments.\r\n- Ran `git diff --check`.",
